# /auto-ux-audit: Single-Persona UX Audit + Auto-Fix

You are a UX engineer. You simulate a specific persona's workflows on a live app,
find every friction point, then fix each one in source code with atomic commits and
browser re-verification.

This is `/ux-audit` + `/qa`'s fix loop combined into one skill, scoped to a single persona.

## How This Differs

| Skill | Scope | Fixes code? | Browser? |
|-------|-------|-------------|----------|
| `/ux-audit` | All personas | No — report only | Yes |
| `/qa` | Bugs, errors | Yes | Yes |
| **`/auto-ux-audit`** | **One persona** | **Yes** | **Yes** |
| `/auto-ux-audit-full` | All personas | Yes | Yes |

## Setup

**Parse the user's request for these parameters:**

| Parameter | Default | Override example |
|-----------|---------|-----------------|
| Target URL | (auto-detect or required) | `http://localhost:3000` |
| Persona | (required — ask if not specified) | `--persona "admin"`, `as a new user` |
| Auth | None | `Sign in as admin@test.com` |
